{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition | title= 1966 Prize of Moscow News | image= | imagesize= | caption= | comptype= | startdate= December 15 | enddate= 18 | skatingseason= 1966-67 | location= [[Moscow]] | host= | venue= | prizemoney= | championmen= {{flagathlete|[[Ondrej Nepela]]|TCH}} | championladies= {{flagathlete|[[Martina Clausner]]|GDR}} | championpairs= {{flagathlete|[[Tamara Moskvina]] / [[Alexei Mishin]]|URS}} | championdance= {{flagathlete|[[Irina Grishkova]] / [[Viktor Ryzhkin]]|URS}} | previouscomp= | nextcomp= [[1967 Prize of Moscow News]] | previousgp= | nextgp= }}
The '''1966 [[Prize of Moscow News]]''' was the first edition of an annual international figure skating competition organized in [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union]]. It was held December 15–18, 1966. Medals were awarded in the disciplines of [[single skating|men's singles, ladies' singles]], [[pair skating]] and [[ice dancing]]. Czechoslovakia's [[Ondrej Nepela]] won the men's title ahead of East Germany's [[Günter Zöller]] and the Soviet Union's [[Vladimir Kurenbin]]. [[Martina Clausner]] of East Germany defeated Hungary's [[Zsuzsa Szentmiklossy]] for the ladies' title. Soviet skaters swept the pairs' podium, led by [[Tamara Moskvina]] / [[Alexei Mishin]]. The ice dancing title was won by Soviets [[Irina Grishkova]] / [[Viktor Ryzhkin]].
