{{Infobox Sports league | title = Lingerie Basketball League | logo = | pixels = | sport = [[Basketball]] | founded = 2011 | folded = 2013 | ceo = Nina Kako | inaugural = 2011 | current_season = | upcoming_season = | motto = | teams = 4 | country = {{USA}} | champion = | most_champs = | website = | TV = }} The '''Lingerie Basketball League''' ('''LBL''') was a women's [[basketball]] [[sports league|league]], created in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thebiglead.com/2011/08/01/lingerie-basketball-poised-to-replace-the-wnba/|title=Lingerie Basketball Poised to Replace The WNBA|date=2011-08-01|website=The Big Lead|access-date=2017-03-09}}</ref> The Lingerie Basketball League was set up after the success of the [[Legends Football League]], originally called the Lingerie Football League. Like the LFL, players in the LBL wear revealing outfits instead of traditional uniforms.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2025835/Lingerie-Basketball-League-Los-Angeles-hopes-lure-male-fans.html|title=Slam dunk against feminism? Lingerie basketball hopes to lure male fans but there might not be too many women at the games|work=Mail Online|access-date=2017-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2011/08/05/lingerie-athletic-leagues-are-proof-that-women-have-long-way-to-go-to-equality.html|title=Lingerie Athletic Leagues Are Proof That Women, Men Are Hardly Equal in Sports, Experts Say|last=McKay|first=Hollie|date=2011-08-05|work=Fox News|access-date=2017-03-09|language=en-US}}</ref>
The Lingerie Basketball League held its inaugural season in 2011 with four [[Los Angeles]] based teams. The L.A. Beauties won the first championship.{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}
The LBL held a second season in 2012, but there was no championship game. A championship game between the L.A. Divas and L.A. Glam was announced, but never held.{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}
The LBL did not play in 2013 and is currently inactive.
