{{Orphan|date=September 2015}}
'''Raw Run''' is recognized colloquially within the [[longboarding]] community as a recorded video showcasing the entire descent down a hill, from top to bottom. This is typically done all in one [[take]] to showcase the rider's consistency and skill.
== Notable Examples ==
[[Colorado]] native and longboarder, Zak Maytum,<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://blogs.denverpost.com/sports/2015/09/09/watch-zak-maytum-longboards-near-70-mph-in-colorado/28161/|title = WATCH: Zak Maytum longboards near 70 mph in Colorado|date = September 9, 2015|accessdate = September 9, 2015|website = WATCH: Zak Maytum longboards near 70 mph in Colorado|publisher = The Denver Post|last = Nguyen|first = Joe}}</ref> made national news when a video of him descending a roadway reportedly achieving 70&nbsp;mph went [[Viral video|viral]]. The [[YouTube]] video titled "Raw Run: Zak Maytum" reached one million views in under two days.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5fOVXndyjAo|title = Raw Run: Zak Maytum|date = 2015-09-08|accessdate = 2015-09-09|website = Raw Run: Zak Maytum|publisher = Youtube|last = |first = }}</ref>
