{{Infobox award
|year = 2017
|holder = [[Dikembe Mutombo]]
|presenter = [[NBA Awards]]
}}
The '''Sager Strong Award''' is an annual award given by the [[National Basketball Association]]. It is presented to "an individual who has been a trailblazer while exemplifying courage, faith, compassion, and grace." The award was created in 2017 to honor of the longtime NBA sideline reporter [[Craig Sager]] (1951-2016), and the recipient receives a replica of the colorful [[sports coat]] that Sager wore when accepting the 2016 [[Jimmy V Award]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dikembe Mutombo to receive Craig Sager Strong Award|url=http://www.nba.com/article/2018/05/22/dikembe-mutombo-receive-craig-sager-strong-award|website=NBA.com|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref>

